.\" algocli.1 — man page for the AlgoBackup admin shell.
.\" Format: BSD mdoc.  Render: man -l algocli.1
.Dd April 25, 2026
.Dt ALGOCLI 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm algocli
.Nd interactive admin shell for the AlgoBackup appliance
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the privileged readline shell that operators use to administer an
AlgoBackup appliance: managing backup points, NFS shares, SSH/FTP/web
access control, filesystem quotas, and basic system operations
(reboot, shutdown, MOTD).
.Pp
The binary is installed setuid root.
At startup it drops effective uid back to the invoking user and
re-escalates only around the specific syscalls that need root
.Pq Xr reboot 2 ,
.Xr fork 2 + Xr execve 2
of root-owned tools, writes under
.Pa /etc .
Every state-changing command is gated by PAM re-authentication.
Authentication attempts and command outcomes are written to
.Pa /tmp/algocli-audit.log .
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width ".Fl Fl version"
.It Fl h , Fl Fl help
Print a short usage message and exit.
.It Fl v , Fl Fl version
Print the build version string and exit.
.El
.Sh COMMANDS
At the prompt, type
.Ic help
for the full top-level command list, or any command name to see its
sub-commands.
The most-used commands:
.Bl -tag -width ".Ic accessctrl"
.It Ic bp Ar verb Op Ar args
Backup-point lifecycle:
.Ic bp create | delete | rename | list ,
plus
.Ic bp quota set Ar bp Ar limit .
Names must match
.Bq Pa A-Z a-z 0-9 _ . -
and be 1\(en64 characters.
.It Ic fs quota Ar verb
Filesystem-level btrfs quota controls
.Pq Ic enable | disable | status .
.It Ic nfs Ar verb Op Ar args
NFS export operations:
.Ic enable | disable | share | unshare | list .
Hosts must be valid RFC-1123 names.
.It Ic accessctrl Ar svc Ar verb Op Ar args
Service ACLs.
.Ar svc
is one of
.Ic ssh | ftp | web .
Each supports
.Ic enable | disable | set ;
.Ic ssh
also has
.Ic add allowed-host , del allowed-host , list .
.It Ic system Ar verb
.Ic reboot | shutdown | set motd .
Reboot/shutdown require an interactive y/N confirmation in addition
to PAM auth.
.Ic set motd
reads MOTD content from stdin until a single
.Ql \&.
line or EOF, then atomically replaces
.Pa /etc/motd .
.It Ic log Ar verb
.Ic list | view Ar file | watch Ar file .
Read-only; does not require auth.
.It Ic exit
Leave the shell.
.El
.Sh AUTHENTICATION
Every state-changing command runs
.Xr pam_authenticate 3
under the PAM service named
.Pa algocli .
A PAM service file must therefore exist at
.Pa /etc/pam.d/algocli ;
the
.Cm make install
target lays down a default that delegates to
.Pa system-auth .
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width ".Pa /tmp/algocli-audit.log"
.It Pa /mnt/backup
Default backup root (override at build time with
.Fl D Ar BACKUP_ROOT ) .
.It Pa /mnt/support
Default log-view directory
.Pq Fl D Ar LOG_VIEW_DIR .
.It Pa /etc/motd
Target file for
.Ic system set motd .
.It Pa /etc/pam.d/algocli
PAM service file consulted by the auth gate.
.It Pa registry.db
Sqlite3 configuration store.
Resolved relative to the working directory by default; override with
.Fl D Ar REGISTRY_PATH_DEFAULT .
.It Pa $XDG_STATE_HOME/algocli/history
Readline history (capped at 1000 entries).
Falls back to
.Pa $HOME/.local/state/algocli/history
then
.Pa /tmp/algocli/history .
.It Pa /tmp/algocli-audit.log
Audit trail of authentication attempts and privileged-command
outcomes.
.It Pa /tmp/<context>.log
Per-context operation logs
.Po Pa bp.log , Pa fs.log , Pa nfs.log , ... Pc .
.El
.Sh SECURITY NOTES
The shell takes adversarial input seriously.
All command arguments cross input validators
.Pq Pa validate.h
before reaching the registry or any spawned subprocess.
SQL is constructed exclusively via
.Xr sqlite3_prepare_v2 3
with bound parameters; no user-supplied byte ever reaches the SQL
parser.
Subprocesses are launched via
.Xr execve 2
with absolute paths and a sanitized environment
.Pq clearenv + curated allowlist ;
no shell metacharacter has any meaning.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width ".It 64"
.It 0
Success
.Pq normal exit, Fl Fl help , Fl Fl version .
.It 64
Usage error (unknown flag).
.It other
Command-specific failure
.Pq see audit log .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr btrfs 8 ,
.Xr pam.conf 5 ,
.Xr systemctl 1 ,
.Xr sqlite3 1
